analyse-availability: Availability = Run Time / Planned Production Time
analyse-fully-productive-time-definition: The ideal time in order to manufacture given number of A quality products.
analyse-hidden-factory: Hidden Factory = All Time - Fully Productive Time
analyse-hidden-factory-definition: Subtraction of Fully Productive Time from given time
analyse-oee1: Oee1 = Availability x Actual Performance x Quality
analyse-oee2: Oee2 = Availability x Worked Performance x Quality
analyse-planned-production-time-definiti: It is the operating time that is outside the planned stop times within the examined time period.
analyse-planned-standby-time-definition: It is the sum of the intersections between the time the machine is in the Standby status and the times when the workstation is in the Planned stop status with in the examined time period
analyse-quality-definition: It is the ratio of the quantity of 1st quality product to the total production amount produced within the given range
analyse-run-time-definition: It is the sum of the times when the machine is in running status within the examined time period.
analyse-standby-time-definition: It is the sum of the times when the machine is in StandBy status within the examined time period.
analyse-unplanned-stop-duration-definiti: It is the sum of the intersections between the time the machine is in the Standby status and the times when the workstation is in the Unplanned stop status with in the examined time period
analyse-utilization: Utilization = Planned Production Time / All Time
analyse-utilization-definition: It is the ratio of the time of planned production within the given range to duration of given range
analyse.production-order.capacity-effici: Total # of products in quality A / Total # of produced.
Capacity Efficiency = The quantity produced in A quality / The quantity expected for ideal case [in given time span]
analyse.production-order.down-time-defin: The closing time of machine after production ends (cooling, cleaning, mould exchange etc.) After the job is finished, the idle time of the machine without any reason is not included in this period before adding a new job
analyse.production-order.job-waiting-tim: Job Waiting Time = Down time + Setup time
analyse.production-order.min-preparing-t: Min preparation time to process single item of the job order.
analyse.production-order.net-working-tim: The total amount of time when machine is in active production.
Net Working Time = Running Time + Total Preparing Time
analyse.production-order.quality-perform: Quality Performance = # of products in quality A / Total # of products
analyse.production-order.quantity-effici: Planned Quantity is calculated by this formula: (Total # of Planned Quantity / Total Duration of Job Order) * Examined Range Duration. Note: direct proportion
Quantity Efficiency = Produced quantity in quality A / Planned quantity
analyse.production-order.quantity-perfor: Quantity Performance = (Produced quantity – Scrap etc. quantity) / Planned quantity
analyse.production-order.running-time-de: The sum of times when the machine is running in the time from beginning of the job to the end of the job.
analyse.production-order.setup-time-defi: Period required to prepare a device, machine, process, or system for it to be ready to function or accept a job. It is a subset of cycle time.
analyse.production-order.single-product-: Sing. Prod. Cycle Time = The ideal time required for manufacturing single product.
The average time in practice for manufacturing single product.
The power consumption for manufacturing single product.
The energy cost for manufacturing single product.
analyse.production-order.total-preparing: The total preparation time for machine to process the job order.
analyse.workstation.machine-occupancy-de: It provides rate information on how much of the working time interval is occupied with the respective machine. For instance, machine worked 24 hours, how many hours of 24 hours was it occupied with the machine?
analyse.workstation.machine-occupancy-fo: Machine Occupancy = (All Time Range - Total Idle duration of Machine) / All Time Range
analyse.workstation.time-efficiency-defi: The ratio of running duration to time when machine is in active prouction
analyse.workstation.time-efficiency-form: Time Efficiency = Running Duration / Running Duration + Preparing Time
